            We think that current arrangements work well and that the independence, which we all value, will be underpinned. I agree that we need to deal with perceptions. I think that we can do that. The commission, in grasping the nettle, the need and the urgency for reform, has begun clearly to demonstrate that in improving its operation and aspiring to carry on with that further improvement.</p><p>
