            <q>So far as is reasonably practicable the Commission must, in performing its functions, act in a way,</q>
            but also "in performing its functions and meeting its objectives". That would extend that, and it would go some way to meeting the point made by the noble Lord, Lord Hodgson.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0669P0-02854'>
